Nice spot, great bartenders but I had the worst experience there last night. Went in early to see the Wilder vs Fury fight. We got there early and got seats at the bar but as the time drew closer for the main event the place moved from sparsely populated to overcrowded . The place was packed to capacity and yet they kept collecting and stuffing more people inside. It got dangerous so I requested my entry fee and left. Hey Bleachers, you have a great thing going please do not allow greed to get you shut down like many other great spots we've seen this happen to in Brooklyn. Respect the fire code and make the experience comfortable.

Good happy hour deals and appetizers. Nice seating, not too busy during day time and the doors open wide during warmer months for outside like seating. Very close to Barclays center, so maybe pregame here or go here after a game.
